last_release: 2026-06-13 v2.10.0 (PR #32 bundle + #33 review fixes feature→dev, PR #34 dev→main merge e478fca; release https://github.com/Data-Wise/rforge/releases/tag/v2.10.0; CI green on main RForge CI + Deploy Documentation; docs live-verified v2.10.0 + /reference/{s7review,scaffold,changed}/ + /tutorials/scaffolding-existing-packages/ all HTTP 200; tap PR Data-Wise/homebrew-tap#121 MERGED — formula+manifest → v2.10.0, sha256 96ef1108…, desc 35→39, ruby -c OK, --diff only pre-existing bin.mkpath drift). Three-feature bundle (35→39 commands): #26 r:s7-review + scaffolding r:use-* + diff-aware --changed (scope-only). Hardened by a pre-release adversarial review that caught + fixed 3 bug-classes the gates missed (diff-aware false-negative, deps_sync constraint-drop, s7review FPs). pytest 298, test-all 41/41.
in_progress_prior: 2026-06-13 v2.10.0 — review-hardened. Adversarial review of the bundle (5 dims, 2-lens verify) before release caught 3 real bug-classes the TDD gates missed, all FIXED via PR #33 (merge d7bd31b): (1) BLOCKER diff-aware --changed silent false-negative — _run_check_at ignored its ref (HEAD vs HEAD) so r:check --changed reported ok with real ERRORs; now honest scope-only, tagging deferred, real-git e2e test replaces the mocked one that hid it; (2) deps_sync _apply_patch dropped version constraints on --write (corrupted DESCRIPTION; affected r:use-package AND r:deps-sync since v2.5.0) — now preserves verbatim specs; (3) s7review 4 false positives (no comment/string masking; new_property flagged as type) — added masking seam. pytest 290→298; test-all 41/41. Lesson saved [[feedback_adversarial_review_prose_contracts]]. ---- Bundle (PR #32, merge 85881e8): #26 r:s7-review (+1) + scaffolding r:use-* (+3) + diff-aware --changed (+0). #26 r:s7-review (lib/s7review.py, cranlint archetype, 5 advisory families; --eco/R-pass deferred; +1) + scaffolding r:use-test/use-package/use-vignette (lib/scaffold.py+usethis_infra.py, dry-run default + --write, reuses deps_sync._apply_patch/scan_usage; +3) + diff-aware --changed (lib/changed.py, flags on r:check/test/lint, merge-base 2nd-check deferred; +0). 35→39 commands; test-all 36→41; pytest 232→290. Built by 3 sequential implementer agents + a docs gap-pass agent in one bundle worktree; mkdocs --strict clean. Specs+plans in docs/specs/. NEXT: dev→main release PR + tap sync (or bundle more first).
last_release_prior: 2026-06-12 v2.9.0 (PR #29+#30 feature→dev, PR #31 dev→main merge c747b24, release https://github.com/Data-Wise/rforge/releases/tag/v2.9.0; CI green on main RForge CI + Deploy Documentation; docs live-verified v2.9.0 + /orchestrator/ HTTP 200; tap PR Data-Wise/homebrew-tap#120 MERGED — formula+manifest → v2.9.0, sha256 08c45b9b…, ruby -c OK; --diff shows only pre-existing bin.mkpath drift, no new version/sha drift). Phase 4 orchestrator rewrite (last craft-parity item): stale agents/orchestrator.md (13 removed rforge_* MCP tools) → python3 -m lib.* delegation, 7 intents, read-only/recommend-only safety gate, per-module synthesis; +3 test-all guards (33→36, incl. recipe validator). Validated by TWO adversarial review workflows (caught 2 blockers in draft + 1 self-introduced in the fix). Bundled: #20 Ecosystem.manifest_order + #26 r:s7-review spec (post-v2.9.0 candidate) + orchestrator docs (guide/cookbook/REFCARD/homepage) + commands.md count fix + argument-hint inline help on 10 r: commands. 232 pytest + test-all 36/36. 35 commands (no surface change).
